				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP005_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>
						<hi rend="letter-spacing: +2px">Statement</hi>
					</p>
					<p>Written with Mr. <hi rend="letter-spacing: +2px"><persName ref="#ehri_et_kulka_erich">Erich Schön</persName></hi>, born <date when="1911-02-18">18. 2. 1911</date>, residing in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3062339/vsetin.html">Vsetín</placeName>, Žerotínova 992,
						former <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoner</term> of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3065525/spilberk.html">Spielberg</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177">Dachau</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-685"
							>Hamburg-Neuengamme</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0">Auschwitz</placeName> and <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Birkenau</placeName>, profession <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-4" type="subject">clerk</term>, Czech nationality.</p>
					<p>Report on the tragic fate of <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Jakub Edelstein’s</persName> family.</p>
					<p>On <date when="1943-12-20">December 20th, 1943</date>, roughly 5,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, and <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>, most of them <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-279" type="subject">Czech Jews</term>, arrived in <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz-Birkenau</placeName> from the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt ghetto</placeName>. They were placed in the special so-called Czech
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">Family Camp in Birkenau</term>, section <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">B-II-B</term>.</p>
					<p>Amongst them was the family of <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Jakub Edelstein</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>.</p>
					<p>However, <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Jakub Edelstein</persName>, together with three companions, was called away from the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-267" type="subject">transport</term> at the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName> train station and brought by car to the main camp <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1">Auschwitz I</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Here, they were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">imprisoned</term> in block no. 11, the so-called <q>Bunker</q>, which was used as an investigation <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483"
							type="subject">prison</term> by the camp <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350" type="subject">Gestapo</term>, the so-called Politische Abteilung. Few made it out alive from there. It contained all kinds of instruments of torture, which were
						used to force either true or false confessions from the accused. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">Executions</term> took place in the courtyard of this block.</p>
					<p><persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Edelstein</persName> was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-634" type="subject">interrogated</term> several times and accused of enabling the
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term> of several people from the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt ghetto</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Meanwhile, his family was in camp <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">B-II-b</term>. His <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296998">wife</persName> worked at the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-595" type="subject">children’s home</term>, which was overseen by <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1459810" type="victim">Fredy Hirsch</persName>.
						She, along with her mother and <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296634" type="victim">child</persName> was faring quite well. Through <persName ref="#ehri_et_jakub">Jakub</persName>, who was a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">guard</term> in block no. 11, we managed to put <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Jakub Edelstein</persName>
							in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1">Auschwitz I</placeName> in contact with his family in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">Birkenau</term>. Two <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-716" type="subject">letters</term> were exchanged in secret.</p>
					<p>Sometime in <date when="1944-02">February 1944</date>, high-ranking <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> officer <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000564">Eichmann</persName> of the
							<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-427">RSHA</orgName> arrived in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">Auschwitz-Birkenau</term>. He spoke with  <persName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1459810" type="victim">Fredy Hirsch</persName> and <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1485316" type="victim">Janowitz</persName>, was briefed on
						the conditions in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="subject">camp</term>, and asked to see <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Edelstein’s</persName>
						<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296998">wife</persName>.</p>
					<p>He asked her how she was doing and whether she had a request. He also asked her whether she knew about her <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">husband</persName>. She requested to be allowed to see her
							<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">husband</persName>. He promised she would be able to do so at a later date and asked her to write a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-716" type="subject">letter</term> to her <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">husband</persName>, which he promised to deliver.
							<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Edelstein</persName> was supposedly somewhere in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Reich</term>.</p>
					<p>About one month after his departure, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-698" type="subject">liquidation</term> of the Czech <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">Family
							Camp</term> took place. On <date when="1944-03-08">March 8th</date>, 3,860 men, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject"
							>children</term> from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-267" type="subject">transports</term> of <date when="1943-09-07">September 7th</date> and <date when="1943-09-09">9th, 1943</date>, were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-698" type="subject">annihilated</term> in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-698" type="subject">gas chambers</term> of <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">Crematorium</term> I and II.</p>
					<p>We found out that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term> of the Czech <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">Family Camp</term> were ordered <q><distinct
								type="camp_language"><foreign xml:lang="de">Sonderbehandlung (SB)</foreign></distinct></q> after being in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-168" type="subject">quarantine</term> for half a year. According to this, the second
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-698" type="subject">liquidation</term> was then expected on <date when="1944-06-20">June 20th, 1944</date>.</p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP005_02.jpg" n="2"/>
					<p>The second <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-698" type="subject">liquidation</term> took place a short time later, but it it began exactly on <date when="1944-06-20">June 20th</date> with the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">annihilation</term> of the <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Edelstein</persName> family, which happened like this:</p>
					<p>On <date when="1944-06-20">June 20th</date> in the afternoon, a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prison</term> transport vehicle (paddy wagon) arrived in front of block no. 11 in <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1">Auschwitz I</placeName>. The escorting <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> man from Politische Abteilung requested that <persName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Jakub Edelstein</persName> and his companions be brought to him. He told the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">guard</term>
						that they would be released to the Czech <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">Family Camp</term> and took their personal files with them. They told <persName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Edelstein</persName> that he would go to his family.</p>
					<p>They were taken away by car, but not to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">Family Camp</term>. In fact, they were brought to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject"
							>Crematorium</term> III in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Birkenau</placeName>.</p>
					<p>The same car then drove to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-594" type="subject">Family Camp</term>, from where it was supposed to take <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855"
							type="victim">Edelstein’s</persName>
						<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296998">wife</persName> and his family. That same day, <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">E</persName>.’s <persName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296998">wife</persName>, gravely <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term>, lay in block no. 32. The <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctor</term> refused to release her with the explanation that she was unable to be transported. The car left.</p>
					<p>A few minutes later, the car returned with a strict order by <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001244">Schwarzhuber</persName>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject"
							>commander</term> of the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0">camp</placeName>, that Mrs. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296998">Edelstein</persName> and her family must be released immediately in
						the state that she was in.</p>
					<p>They were also brought to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">Crematorium</term> III. There, all of them were then <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot to death</term> in the
						execution hall and burned in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term>.</p>
					<p>This statement can be verified by the eyewitnesses who have returned:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_muller_filip">Filip Müller</persName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057685/sereg.html">Sered n. Váhom</placeName>, who saw the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">execution</term> in <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">Crematorium</term> III., <persName ref="#ehri_et_neumann_josef">Josef Neumann</persName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3056508/zilina.html">Žilina</placeName>, was was a prisoner in
						block 11 in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0">Auschwitz</placeName> and spoke with <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1296855" type="victim">Jakub Edelstein</persName>.</p>
					<p>Signature:</p>
					<p>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_kulka_erich">Erich Schön</persName>
					</p>
